Appendix item 17: Control Principle 2. Human overrides are expected. The system should require explicit reason codes and actor identity rather than pretending the algorithm is always right. Include this context when reasoning about tradeoffs, state transitions, operator responsibilities, evidence retention, and rollout risk.

Appendix item 18: Reliability Principle 1. Idempotent handlers and append-only events are preferred because retries, delayed uploads, and duplicated external feeds are normal. Include this context when reasoning about tradeoffs, state transitions, operator responsibilities, evidence retention, and rollout risk.

Appendix item 19: Reliability Principle 2. Operator remediation hints are part of the product, not optional documentation. If a job fails silently, the workflow is incomplete. Include this context when reasoning about tradeoffs, state transitions, operator responsibilities, evidence retention, and rollout risk.

